Since I was extending the `Record` class, I need to define a constructor in the sub class that takes in all the required parameters.

Here&#39;s a small example as to what I was doing (**Incorrect entity implementation**):
```
@Entity(tableName = &quot;Items&quot;)
public class Item extends Record {

    @ColumnInfo(name = &quot;Something&quot;)
    private final String something;

