This is a valid sub-class and java compiler won&#39;t complain, however `room` simply cannot find a valid constructor with all the three required fields `(id, createdDate, something)` which it needs to initialise the object `Item` from the database.

Instead this is how we need to define any subclass.
```
@Entity(tableName = &quot;Items&quot;)
public class Item extends Record {

    @ColumnInfo(name = &quot;Something&quot;)
    private final String something;

    public Item(long id, long createdDate, long @NonNull String something) {
        super(id, createdDate);
        this.something = something;
    }
}
```

